Let's Start Learning Shell_Scripting

------------------------------------------------
first : Make any particular dir
mkdir myfirstscript

second: go to that directory
cd myfirstscript

third: create file
  $vim first.sh

fourth: start writing into first.sh
    #!/bin/bash
    echo "What is your name"
    read a1            ("it is use for taking input)
    echo "your name is $a1"

output:::: your name is mayuri

five : save and come out of vim editor

six: give permission to execute file 
  $chmod 700 first.sh

seven: run the file 
  $./ first.sh  or bash first.sh


